In the evening, when the air is cool,
And the river runs along the shore,
I hear the whispers of the leaves,
Each a story of the world before.

Nature speaks loud to those who hear,
The stillness is alive with song,
Come join the eternal dance,
For here is where we all belong.


- Walt Whitman
